---
/**
 * MapPin — forest-green brand map marker overlaid on a Google iframe embed.
 * Usage: place <MapPin /> as a child of a `.cag-map-wrap` element that wraps
 * the map <iframe>. The teardrop tip sits at the map's center point, covering
 * Google's default red marker so the location reads in brand color. The free
 * `output=embed` iframe can't recolor its own pin, so this overlay is the
 * no-API-key way to match a custom-pin look. Decorative (aria-hidden); does
 * not capture pointer events, so the underlying map stays fully interactive.
 * Note: the pin is anchored to map-center, so it does not follow if a visitor
 * drags the map — intended for a fixed "here we are" location embed.
 */
---
<span class="cag-map-pin" aria-hidden="true">
  <svg width="34" height="45" viewBox="0 0 24 32" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" role="img" aria-label="C.A.Gs location — Midland, TX">
    <path d="M12 0C5.373 0 0 5.373 0 12c0 9 12 20 12 20s12-11 12-20C24 5.373 18.627 0 12 0z" fill="#2D6A4F" />
    <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="4.6" fill="#ffffff" />
  </svg>
</span>

<style is:global>
  .cag-map-wrap { position: relative; }
  .cag-map-wrap .cag-map-pin {
    position: absolute;
    left: 50%;
    top: 50%;
    transform: translate(-50%, -100%);
    pointer-events: none;
    z-index: 2;
    line-height: 0;
    filter: drop-shadow(0 3px 4px rgba(60, 30, 10, 0.45));
  }
</style>
